snippet.textDisplay: Top Gun was moved to Fallon, Nevada, Naval Air Station several years ago.  The flying scenes were done by navy pilots here at Fallon NAS.  The plane that is shown as you say  "on a stick" is in Fallon down the street from where I live.  It is not the entry gate to anything. The plane shown is actually in front of a car lot. There is a bombing practice site here and it is used every day.  I enjoy living here watching and listening to the jets all day.  The credits at the end of the first movie show the real men and call signs of the navy personnel that actually flew to make the movie.
